evidence: "CALSAGOS (Clustering ALgorithmS Applied to Galaxies in Overdense Systems) is a python package developed to select cluster members and to search, find and identify substructures and galaxy groups..."
Example usage shows it imported as a module: "from calsagos import lagasu" and other functions, indicating it is used as a library in user scripts.

Installation and use are via cloning and setup.py: "python3 setup.py install" and tests run with "python3 test.py", with no mention of PyPI or other registries, implying distribution from the source repository.
